raw_data.title: Analyst Junior
raw_data.description: The Analyst Junior works directly with internal customers to understand the environment and information technology needs. Identifies relevant design, process and specification issues and then documents and translates these requirements. Plans and conducts the analysis of business problems to be solved with automated IT systems. Decomposes high level business requirements into systems use cases. Identifies, evaluates, and develops functional requirements and specifications. The Analyst Junior uses available computer systems resources and personnel to carry out analysis to support management's quest for performance improvement to determine the most useful solutions.
